info.headline: Wind Advisory issued October 05 at 3:07PM CDT until October 06 at 1:00PM CDT by NWS Omaha
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 7 AM TO 1 PM CDT FRIDAY... ...FREEZE WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM LATE FRIDAY NIGHT THROUGH SATURDAY MORNING... * WHAT...For the Wind Advisory, northwest winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts up to 45 mph expected. For the Freeze Watch, sub-freezing temperatures as low as 28 possible. * WHERE...Burt, Antelope, Cedar, Cuming, Knox, Madison, Pierce, Stanton, Thurston, and Wayne Counties. * WHEN...For the Wind Advisory, from 7 AM to 1 PM CDT Friday. For the Freeze Watch, from late Friday night through Saturday morning. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds will blow around unsecured objects. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result. Frost and freeze conditions could kill crops, other sensitive vegetation and possibly damage unprotected outdoor plumbing.
info.instruction: Winds this strong can make driving difficult, especially for high profile vehicles. Use extra caution. Secure outdoor objects. Take steps now to protect tender plants from the cold. To prevent water pipes from freezing; wrap or drain or allow them to drip slowly.
